E
part1~
The astral plane is a realm of existance, just as that is true of the
Prime Material Plane, and the Negative Material Plane. The Prime Material
Plane is made up of the world most commonly known to the everyday mortals.
It consists of the elements of earth, air, fire, and water. It also
comprises the plane where most mortals will spend their entire lives, with
no knowledge of the existance of the other two. On very rare occasions,
the barrier between these realms of existance is very thin. At times, it
doesn't even exist. That is how, you adventurer, have stumbled upon this
vortex. Consider yourself lucky. Most mortals never find these connections.
Let it be forsaid, this is an area of chaos. The inhabitants of this
realm do not take lightly to intruders, and most likely will attack at
the very sight of those they refer to as "outsiders."
If you wish to read about these inhabitants, turn to part2.
~
E
part2~
The most important inhabitant of the Astral Plane is the High Overlord
himself. Legend holds that he dwells in a keep somewhere in the AP, but
as of yet, no one has survived to tell about it, or if they did, the
High Overlord made sure that they could never return to the Prime Material
Plane. Some say he transformed them into the denziens of lesser creatures
that now serve him, or left them in human form, but robbed them of their 
soul. They are more dead than alive, and serve him as slaves, more or 
less, in his keep. Rumor holds most he killed, but some he made his personal
guard. Such did these adventurers boldness moved him. Seldom does this 
happen though.
As for the other creatures, the most important ones are the High Overlord
and his brother...or brothers. Ancient accounts hold that he may have 
two brothers that hold as much power as their sibling. They command the
soldiers and the knights. 
The lesser creatures include the etheral wraiths, his witches basically,
~
E
part2i~
the denziens, who are his pets. He also holds in his service a cleric,
and also a mage who serve as advisors to all the brothers.
There are other creatures, but not much is known about them.
~
E
book~
This is a book on the Astral Plane. It is divided into part1 and part2,
with part2 comprising of part2 and part2i
